channel.title: Putting The server online
channel.description:
Well. I have my no-ip thing all set up and running. [i]I[/i] can get on my server fine and well using the no-ip adress (but for me its hopto.org idk why) But I try to put it on the Server status page, but it says: "your server must be online to register a server."
WTF help me

item.title: Putting The server online
item.dc:creator: @Tenacious_T Tenacious T
item.description:
@Tenacious_T wrote:

- If you have router - If its not that then you should go to your router at 192.168.1.1 or 192.62.1.1 idk the others... but try those and if a screen pops up with a Username: and Password: put admin in both but if that dont work ask your parents that information and go in there and look for applications and gaming and put this in application name Mopar and put the rest 43594 or your port for your server... and put TCP and a "3" after 192.168.1. And save settings and if that dont work, sorry... That is a really bad port forwarding tutorial i just did a quick one if you need a better one use tabs..

Actually try to put RSPS in the first text box make sure you set it to TCP and UCD. then go to start run and type CMD then type in IPCONFIG so you can get your router IP cuz u will need it cuz there will be a part on there like this.

192.168.1(then a textbox) you will need to type the rest of your router IP there.
